article.description: Javon Johnson and Umoja Gibson combined for all of DePaul's 18 overtime points and the Blue Demons defeated Loyola Chicago 78-72 on Saturday.
article.headline: Johnson, DePaul take down Loyola Chicago 78-72 in OT
article.linkText: Johnson, DePaul take down Loyola Chicago 78-72 in OT
article.story: Javon Johnson and Umoja Gibson combined for all of DePaul's 18 overtime points and the Blue Demons defeated Loyola Chicago 78-72 on Saturday. Johnson scored 27 points, 10 in overtime, and had six assists for the Blue Demons (5-3). Gibson finished with 23 points, making 4 of 5 from 3-point range, and made four steals. Jalen Terry scored 11 points. Marquise Kennedy led the Ramblers (3-5) with 26 points, hitting four 3-pointers. Tom Welch added 13 points, seven rebounds and two steals for Loyola Chicago. Braden Norris had 11 points and seven assists. A three-point play by Welch with 1:09 left in regulation tied the game at 60-all. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
